comments: Westbrook (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Embiid (PHI).

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Replay review of the OOB called on Milton (PHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. James (LAL) touches the ball last before it goes OOB.
Westbrook (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Harden (PHI) during his drive.
Embiid (PHI) goes to, not through, Davis' (LAL) space and marginal contact occurs as the two come together.
James (LAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Embiid (PHI) initiates contact with James' (LAL) left arm, which affects his SQBR during the driving shot attempt.
Beverley (LAL) initiates body contact with Harden (PHI) and affects Harden's SQBR.
Davis (LAL) is moving alongside Embiid's (PHI) path and marginal body contact occurs  during the drive.
James (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball prior to Embiid's (PHI) pass.
Westbrook (LAL) initiates contact with Embiid's (PHI) left arm during the rebound that dislodges Embiid from his position.
Thybulle (PHI) falls to the floor as a result of incidental foot contact with Westbrook (LAL) during his drive.
Thybulle (PHI) makes incidental hand on ball contact during Beverley's (LAL) driving shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAL) and Embiid (PHI) engage in marginal arm to arm contact as they pursue the pass.
Beverley (LAL) briefly rests his hands on Embiid's (PHI) back as Embiid reaches for the in-bound pass and marginal contact occurs.
Milton (PHI) initiates illegal contact with Davis' (LAL) head following Davis' pass.
Harris (PHI) releases the in-bound pass within five seconds.
Westbrook (LAL) and Melton (PHI) engage and disengage off-ball prior to release of the in-bound pass.
Westbrook (LAL) commits a take foul on Melton (PHI).
Beverley (LAL) disconcerts Melton (PHI) during his free throw attempt.
Thybulle (PHI) contests the shot and initiates contact with Reaves' (LAL) right leg, affecting the jump shot attempt.

Reaves (LAL) dislodges the ball away from Embiid (PHI) prior to incidental follow-through contact occurring thereafter to Embiid's face. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Harris (PHI) releases the in-bound pass within five seconds.
James (LAL) bats the ball off of an official standing OOB and an OOB is correctly called.
Davis (LAL) and Embiid (PHI) engage in marginal arm to arm contact during the rebound.
Davis (LAL) wraps Embiid's (PHI) opposite-side and affects his FOM during the in-bound pass.
Harris (PHI) initiates contact with Davis' (LAL) left arm, which affects his shot attempt at the basket.
